void OpenfileTest1_1 ()
 Name: OpenFileTest1.1 Description: This test will make sure that a file can be properly opened for writing. It will require a separate manual test harness that will simply check to see if it can open and if a value can be written to it. We will then check the result in the file to what was wrote to it. This is an NORMAL test. Method: Manual. We will have to check the file separately to make sure we were able to write the values properly to the file. Input Data: We will provide a valid filename to the OpenFile method and indicate that we would like to open it for writing purposes. Expected Results: It is expected that the file will be properly opened and that the values wrote to the file can be found in the the file. /summary>
